<% partial 'partials/material_sub_sub_heading' do %>
    Linux
<% end %>

<ol>
    <li>
        Install development tools (g++, make, etc.) for your distribution.
    <ul>
        <li>
            Ubuntu/Debian: <code>sudo apt install build-essential</code>
        </li>
    </ul>
    </li>
    <li>
        To run graphical applications you need to install the development libraries for OpenGL.
    <ul>
        <li>
            Ubuntu/Debian: <code>sudo apt install mesa-common-dev libgl1-mesa-dev</code>
        </li>
    </ul>
    </li>
    <li>
        You need to download and install Qt 5.12 and Qt Creator 4.8.1 with the online installer from <a href="https://www.qt.io/download-qt-installer" title="qt.io" target="_blank">qt.io</a>
    </li>
    <li>
        Download <a href="https://github.com/TestMyQt/Qt-CreatorTMC/releases/download/v3.0/qtcreator-tmc-linux-v3.0.zip" title="Qt Creator TMC Linux plugin">qtcreator-tmc-linux-v3.0.zip</a> and extract it.
    </li>
    <li>
        Copy/move the <code>.so</code> file extracted from the qtcreator-tmc-linux-v3.0.zip to the following path: <code>$QT_INSTALL_DIRECTORY/Tools/QtCreator/lib/qtcreator/plugins/</code>
    </li>
    <li>
        Start Qt Creator, TestMyCode plugin should be visible on the top menu.
    </li>
</ol>

<% partial 'partials/material_sub_sub_heading' do %>
    MacOS
<% end %>

<ol>
    <li>
        First you should have <code>XCode</code> installed from the App store to provide the default MacOS compiling environment.
    </li>
    <li>
        You need to download and install Qt 5.12 and Qt Creator 4.8.1 with the online installer from <a href="https://www.qt.io/download-qt-installer" title="qt.io" target="_blank">qt.io</a>
    </li>
    <li>
        Download <a href="https://github.com/TestMyQt/Qt-CreatorTMC/releases/download/v3.0/qtcreator-tmc-macos-v3.0.zip" title="Qt Creator TMC Mac plugin">qtcreator-tmc-macos-v3.0.zip</a> and extract it.
    </li>
    <li>
        Go to the folder where you installed Qt and Qt Creator with the installer.
        <ul>
            <li>
                Right click on Qt Creator and select "Show Package Contents".
            </li>
            <li>
                Navigate to <code>Contents/PlugIns/</code> under the opened package and copy <code>libTestMyCode.dylib</code> to this folder.
            </li>
        </ul>
    </li>
    <li>
        Start Qt Creator from the icon, TestMyCode plugin should be visible on the top menu.
    </li>
</ol>

